The paper deals with face recognition using deep learning and focuses on the problem of matching NIR (near infrared) images to VIS (visible light) images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves cross-spectral hallucination and low-rank embedding, which are techniques that are commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and optimization (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning models, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.IT.
